'''Salhawas''' is a village in Salhawas [[tehsil]], Matanhail subdistrict, [[Jhajjar district]], [[Haryana]], India, in [[Rohtak division]]. It is {{convert|36|km}} south of the district headquarters at Jhajjar. It has a postal head office.

==Demographics of 2011==
As of [[2011 census of India|2011 India census]], Salhawas had a population of 5962 in 1165 households. Males (3097) constitute 51.94%  of the population and females (2865) 48.05%. Salhawas has an average literacy (3942) rate of 66.11%, lower than the national average of 74%: male literacy (2340) is 59.36%, and female literacy (1602) is 40.63% of total literates (3942). In Salhawas, Jhajjar 13.09% of the population is under 6&nbsp;years of age (781).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/pca/SearchDetails.aspx?Id=64361|title=Census of India 2011|accessdate=27 April 2014}}</ref>

